title WordPress oEmbed Controller Flow\n<size:11>(WP_oEmbed_Controller — REST API Route Registration & Request Handling)</size>

|#E9ECEF|WordPress Bootstrap|
start
:WordPress REST API initialises;
:Instantiate WP_oEmbed_Controller;

note right
  Class is **final** — cannot be subclassed.
  Introduced in WordPress 4.4.0.
end note

:Call register_routes();

|#D4EDDA|oEmbed Controller|
:Apply filter **'oembed_default_width'**\n→ $maxwidth (default: 600);

fork
  :Register REST route\n**GET oembed/1.0/embed**\n• callback: get_item()\n• permission: __return_true (public)\n• args: url (required, URI),\n  format (default: json),\n  maxwidth (default: $maxwidth);
  note right
    Fully **public** endpoint —
    no authentication required.
  end note
fork again
  :Register REST route\n**GET oembed/1.0/proxy**\n• callback: get_proxy_item()\n• permission: get_proxy_item_permissions_check()\n• args: url (required, URI),\n  format (json|xml), maxwidth,\n  maxheight, discover (boolean);
  note right
    Requires **edit_posts** capability
    (Editor role or higher).
  end note
end fork

|#FEFEFE|REST Client|
:Client sends HTTP GET request;

if (Route matched?) then (GET /embed)

  |oEmbed Controller|
  :get_item(WP_REST_Request $request);
  :url_to_postid($request['url'])\n→ $post_id;
  :Apply filter **'oembed_request_post_id'**\n($post_id, $url) → $post_id (override);
  :get_oembed_response_data\n($post_id, $request['maxwidth'])\n→ $data;

  if ($data is falsy?) then (yes)
    |#F8D7DA|Error Handling|
    :Return **WP_Error**\n'oembed_invalid_url' (HTTP 404);
    stop
  else (no)
    |oEmbed Controller|
    :Return oEmbed **$data** array\nto REST client;
    stop
  endif

else (GET /proxy)

  |#FFF3CD|Authorization|
  :get_proxy_item_permissions_check();
  :Check **current_user_can('edit_posts')**;

  if (User has edit_posts capability?) then (no)
    |#F8D7DA|Error Handling|
    :Return **WP_Error** 'rest_forbidden'\nHTTP 401 / 403 via\nrest_authorization_required_code();
    stop
  else (yes)

    |oEmbed Controller|
    :get_proxy_item(WP_REST_Request $request);
    :Get all request params → $args;
    :Unset **$args['_wpnonce']**\n(strip security token before\ncache key generation);

    note right
      Nonce stripped to ensure
      **cache-key stability** across
      nonce rotations.
    end note

    :Compute **$cache_key**\n= 'oembed_' . md5(serialize($args));

    |#D4EDDA|Transient Cache|
    :get_transient($cache_key) → $data;

    if ($data not empty?) then (cache hit)
      :Return cached **$data**\n(early return);
      stop
    else (cache miss)

      |oEmbed Controller|
      :Extract $url = $request['url'];
      :Unset $args['url'];
      :Remap maxwidth → width\n(if set in $args);
      :Remap maxheight → height\n(if set in $args);

      note right
        **maxwidth/maxheight** are remapped
        to **width/height** for
        WP_oEmbed::get_data() compatibility.
      end note

      |#D4EDDA|Local oEmbed Resolver|
      :get_oembed_response_data_for_url\n($url, $args) → $data\n(local site short-circuit);

      if ($data truthy?) then (local match)
        |oEmbed Controller|
        :Return local **$data**\n(early return, no caching needed);
        stop
      else (not local)

        |#CCE5FF|External oEmbed Fetch|
        :_wp_oembed_get_object()\n→ WP_oEmbed singleton;
        :WP_oEmbed::get_data($url, $args)\n→ $data (external provider fetch);

        if ($data === false?) then (fetch failed)

          |oEmbed Controller|
          :WP_Embed::get_embed_handler_html\n($args, $url) → $html\n(classic embed handler fallback);

          if ($html truthy?) then (handler matched)
            :Collect enqueued script srcs\nfrom **$wp_scripts->queue**\n→ $enqueued_scripts;
            :Return **(object)**\n{ provider_name: 'Embed Handler',\n  html: $html,\n  scripts: $enqueued_scripts };
            stop
          else (no handler)
            |#F8D7DA|Error Handling|
            :Return **WP_Error**\n'oembed_invalid_url' (HTTP 404);
            stop
          endif

        else (fetch succeeded)

          |oEmbed Controller|
          :Apply filter **'oembed_result'** via\nWP_oEmbed::data2html($data, $url)\n→ $data->html (rendered HTML);
          :Apply filter **'rest_oembed_ttl'**\n→ $ttl (default: DAY_IN_SECONDS);

          note right
            TTL is **filterable** via
            'rest_oembed_ttl' hook.
            Default = 86400 seconds (1 day).
          end note

          |#D4EDDA|Transient Cache|
          :set_transient($cache_key, $data, $ttl)\n(cache response for future requests);

          |oEmbed Controller|
          :Return oEmbed **$data** object\nto REST client;
          stop
        endif
      endif
    endif
  endif
endif

@enduml
